{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 169 "  See if Maple knows a g
eneral formula for solving general cubic polynomials, i.e. is there a \+
3rd order formula comparable to the quadratic formula?  If so, exhibit
 it. " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 22 "p4=a*x^3+b*x^2+c*x+d; " }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 
1 0 16 "solve (p4=0,x);\n" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#/%#p4G,**
&%\"aG\"\"\")%\"xG\"\"$F(F(*&%\"bGF()F*\"\"#F(F(*&%\"cGF(F*F(F(%\"dGF(
" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 26 "fsolve(a*x^3+b*x^2+c*x+
d);" }}{PARA 8 "" 1 "" {TEXT -1 81 "Error, (in fsolve) number of equat
ions, 1, does not match number of variables, 5\n" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 1 " " }{TEXT 279 111 "Why do you think high school students a
re never asked to remember the general formula for the roots of a cubi
c?" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 315 66 "Because there is no easy general f
ormula for the roots of a cubic." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 113 "4.  Solving Equations in One Variable.  \+
 There are two different commands to direct Maple to solve an equation
:  " }{TEXT 284 5 "solve" }{TEXT -1 5 " and " }{TEXT 285 7 "fsolve." }
}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 35 "They have different purposes.  The " }
{TEXT 286 5 "solve" }{TEXT -1 63 " command attempts to find exact solu
tions.  If the expression  " }{TEXT 288 1 "f" }{TEXT -1 116 "  is defi
ned in terms of only one variable, there are several different ways to
 direct Maple to solve the equation  " }{TEXT 289 5 "f  = " }{TEXT 
290 4 "0.  " }{TEXT -1 54 "The following all cause Maple to solve the \+
equation   " }{TEXT 291 5 "f  = " }{TEXT 292 2 "0." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 16 "       solve(f);" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 18 "       solve(f,x);" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 18 "       solve(f=0);" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 20 "      \+
 solve(f=0,x);" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 349 "Maple makes an assumption that if the coefficients of a \+
polynomial are all given exactly (as integers or rational numbers [rat
ios of integer]), then you are only interested in finding exact soluti
ons.  The Fundamental Theorem of Algebra doesn't guarantee that the so
lutions of  a polynomial can be found exactly, only the polynomial has
 solutions.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 78 "You can force Maple to report additional (approximate) so
lutions by using the " }{TEXT 287 6 "fsolve" }{TEXT -1 45 " command.  \+
(What does the \"f\" stand for?)  In" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 249 "
addition, to forcing Maple to report approximate solutions, you can sp
ecify a field extension (typically real or complex) and require Maple \+
to look for solutions which fit in that field extension.  Also, one ca
n specify a range of x values and force" }{TEXT 295 7 " fsolve" }
{TEXT -1 75 " to only look for solutions in that specified range.  For
 example, compare:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "
> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 16 "fsolve(4*x-x^3);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6%$!+++++?!\"*$\"\"!F'$\"+++++?F%" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> \+
" 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 23 "fsolve(4*x-x^3,x=1..4);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#$\"+++++?!\"*" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 28 "For each of the polynomials " }{XPPEDIT 
18 0 "p[1]" "6#&%\"pG6#\"\"\"" }{TEXT -1 9 " through " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 
"p[14]" "6#&%\"pG6#\"#9" }{TEXT -1 19 ", do the following:" }}{PARA 0 
"" 0 "" {TEXT -1 56 "     a.   solve for all exact roots whereever pos
sible, " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 59 "     b.   find all approximate
 roots to 10 decimal places, " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 43 "     c. \+
 factor each into linear factors.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }
}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 106 "You will need to click on  [> in the to
olbar to obtain new execution lines just below the cursor position." }
}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 
0 12 "digits := 10" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "p[1] :=
 x^2-2;" "6#>&%\"pG6#\"\"\",&*$%\"xG\"\"#F'F+!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 
"> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "factor(x^2-2);" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
